We have the people, the tools, the knowledge, and the determination to end #Ebola in #DRC. What we need is the sustained political commitment of all parties so we can safely access and work with communities to beat the virus & end the suffering & loss of life.]

- Tue 4 Jun 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/sante.gouv.cd/ebola_kivu_04juin19?e=f96cddba3b

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 3 Jun 2019:
- since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2020, with 1926 confirmed and 94 probable. In total, there were 1354 deaths (1260 confirmed and 94 probable) and 542 people cured;
- 305 suspected cases under investigation;
- 12 new confirmed cases, including 4 in Mandima, 2 in Katwa, 2 in Mabalako, 2 in Butembo, 1 in Beni, and 1 in Kalunguta;
- 8 new deaths of confirmed cases: 6 community deaths -- 3 in Mandima, 1 in Butembo, 1 in Katwa, and 1 in Beni -- and 2 ETC deaths -- 1 in Mabalako and 1 in Katwa;
- 3 new recoveries released from ETCs -- 2 in Beni and 1 in Butembo.

News
Security
--------
- The Komanda lab was robbed overnight on 3-4 Jun 2019. The thieves took away 2 laptops, a GeneXpert device used to test samples, and other materials found in the lab.
- A dozen people were killed by suspected rebels during an armed incursion in the neighborhood of Rwangoma, in Beni, which occurred on the night of 3 Jun 2019. Exchanges of fire began in the evening, shortly after the response teams left Rwangoma where they organized a community dialogue. This Tuesday morning [4 Jun 2019], hundreds of protesters took to the streets and several commercial activities were paralyzed in the city. The Beni response teams worked slowly and cautiously, but no response activity was temporarily suspended.

