-Tue 4 Jun 2019. Beni: Anger, paralysis
[Actualite, in French (online translation), abridged, edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/06/04/rdc-colere-paralysie-des-activites-beni-apres-les-tueries-dune-dizaine-de-personnes-par

Activities are paralyzed in the city of Beni in the aftermath of killings of at least 12 civilians by suspected ADF rebels in the Butanuka district of Beu commune.

Drivers of motorcycle taxis invaded the streets to show their anger at the death of 4 of their colleagues. Hundreds of protesters including bikers marched with 2 people to the town hall where they tore the flag of the republic before leaving.

Shops are closed and small businesses that had opened in the morning at Kilokwa Central Market also closed. The situation is similar to the Matonge shopping center in Mulekera commune.

The security system has been reinforced at the town hall. A dozen policemen and soldiers are present on site. The same system is visible at the 30 June [2019] roundabout of Beni on Nyamwisi Boulevard.

